oCommerce Waiting List";s:4:"slug";s:29:"yith-woocommerce-waiting-list";s:15:"premium_constat";s:18:"YITH_WCWTL_PREMIUM";s:4:"file";s:8:"init.php";s:7:"wp_info";a:26:{s:4:"name";s:29:"YITH WooCommerce Waiting List";s:4:"slug";s:29:"yith-woocommerce-waiting-list";s:7:"version";s:5:"1.2.0";s:6:"author";s:44:"<a href="https://yithemes.com/">YITHEMES</a>";s:14:"author_profile";s:39:"https://profiles.wordpress.org/yithemes";s:8:"requires";s:3:"4.0";s:6:"tested";s:5:"4.9.4";s:12:"requires_php";b:0;s:6:"rating";d:58;s:7:"ratings";a:5:{i:5;i:7;i:4;i:0;i:3;i:1;i:2;i:0;i:1;i:8;}s:11:"num_ratings";i:16;s:15:"support_threads";i:3;s:24:"support_threads_resolved";i:1;s:15:"active_installs";i:1000;s:10:"downloaded";i:15081;s:12:"last_updated";s:21:"2018-02-02 1:22pm GMT";s:5:"added";s:10:"2015-04-07";s:8:"homepage";s:65:"https://yithemes.com/themes/plugins/yith-woocommerce-waiting-list";s:8:"sections";a:5:{s:11:"description";s:1945:"<p>What do you do when you have no more stock of one of your products and your customers want to buy it? You risk to lose them, unless you make a system available for them to be notified of the product coming back to stock. Then, why not using a plugin that allows them to be added to a waiting list and being informed in an automatic and efficient way? This is what YITH WooCommerce Waiting List does, allowing you to loyalise them in a simple way and at the same time not lose them.</p>\n<p><strong>Main features:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>A form to receive a reminding email when the item is back in stock</li>\n<li>&#8220;Add me to the waiting list&#8221; button for logged users</li>\n<li>Summary metabox with the number of waiting user and a rapid way to contact them</li>\n<li>Customization of the &#8220;Notify me&#8221; button</li>\n<li>Email basic template to notify users for an item back in stock</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Gợi ý</h3>\n<p>If you have suggestions about how to improve YITH WooCommerce Waiting List, you can <a href="mailto:&#112;&#108;&#x75;&#x67;&#x69;&#x6e;&#x73;&#064;&#121;&#105;&#116;&#104;&#x65;&#x6d;&#x65;&#x73;&#x2e;&#099;&#111;&#109;" title="Your Inspiration Themes" rel="nofollow">write us</a> so we can bundle them into YITH WooCommerce Waiting List.</p>\n<h3>Phiên dịch</h3>\n<h4>Available Languages</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Tiếng Anh</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you can&#8217;t find this plugin in your language and want to translate it, use the dedicated tool at <a href="https://translate.wordpress.org/locale/it/default/wp-plugins/yith-woocommerce-waiting-list" title="Translating WordPress" rel="nofollow">Translating WordPress</a>.<br />\nOr, if you have created your own language pack, or have an update for an existing one, you can send it as an email attachment from our <a href="http://yithemes.com/contact/" title="Your Inspiration Themes" rel="nofollow">Contacts page</a> and we will bundle into YITH WooCommerce Waiting List.</p>\n";s:12:"installation";s:241:"<ol>\n<li>Unzip the downloaded zip file.</li>\n<li>Upload the plugin folder into the <code>wp-content/plugins/</code> directory of your WordPress site.</li>\n<li>Activate <code>YITH WooCommerce Waiting List</code> from Plugins page.</li>\n</ol>\n";s:9:"changelog";s:2798:"<h4>1.2.0</h4>\n<p>Released Feb 02 &#8211; 2018</p>\n<ul>\n<li>New: Support to WooCommerce 3.3.0.</li>\n<li>New: Support to WordPress 4.9.2</li>\n<li>Update: Plugin Core.</li>\n<li>Fix: Product name including variations on plugin&#8217;s emails.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.1.2</h4>\n<p>Released Oct 12 &#8211; 2017</p>\n<ul>\n<li>New: Support to WooCommerce 3.2.0.</li>\n<li>New: Support to WordPress 4.8.2</li>\n<li>Update: Plugin Core.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.1.1</h4>\n<p>Released Apr 21 &#8211; 2017</p>\n<ul>\n<li>New: Support to WooCommerce 3.0.4.</li>\n<li>Update: Plugin Core.</li>\n<li>Fix: Prevent duplicated post meta for product.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.1.0</h4>\n<p>Released Mar 29 &#8211; 2017</p>\n<ul>\n<li>New: Support to WooCommerce 3.0.0 RC2.</li>\n<li>New: Support to WordPress 4.7.3.</li>\n<li>Update: Plugin Core.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0.8</h4>\n<p>Released Jan 13 &#8211; 2017</p>\n<ul>\n<li>New: Shortcode for print waiting list form [yith_wcwtl_form].</li>\n<li>New: Support to WooCommerce 2.6.7.</li>\n<li>New: Support to WordPress 4.7.1.</li>\n<li>Update: Plugin Core.</li>\n<li>Dev: Add filter for form html &#8216;yith_wcwtl_form_html&#8217;.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0.7</h4>\n<p>Released Nov 07 &#8211; 2016</p>\n<ul>\n<li>New: Support to WordPress 4.6.1</li>\n<li>New: Support to WooCommerce 2.6.7</li>\n<li>New: &#8220;In Stock Email Settings&#8221; panel on plugin options.</li>\n<li>New: Option for change email content directly from plugin panel.</li>\n<li>Update: Plugin Core.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0.6</h4>\n<p>Released May 24 &#8211; 2016</p>\n<ul>\n<li>New: Support to WordPress 4.5.2.</li>\n<li>New: Support to WooCommerce 2.6 Beta2.</li>\n<li>Update: Plugin Core.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0.5</h4>\n<p>Released Apr 15 &#8211; 2016</p>\n<ul>\n<li>New: Support to WordPress 4.5.</li>\n<li>Update: Plugin Core.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0.4</h4>\n<p>Released Jan 07 &#8211; 2016</p>\n<ul>\n<li>New: Support to WooCommerce 2.5 BETA.</li>\n<li>Update: Plugin Core.</li>\n<li>Update: Language file .pot.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0.3</h4>\n<p>Released Nov 03 &#8211; 2015</p>\n<ul>\n<li>New: xml config file for wpml.</li>\n<li>Update: Plugin core.</li>\n<li>Update: Language file. Changed text domain from yith-wcwtl to yith-woocommerce-waiting-list.</li>\n<li>Fix: Add users email in BBC ( thanks to jedelucca and Spartan_SA from wordpress support forum ).</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0.2</h4>\n<p>Released Aug 13 &#8211; 2015</p>\n<ul>\n<li>New: Support to WooCommerce 2.4.</li>\n<li>Update: Plugin core.</li>\n<li>Update: Language file.</li>\n<li>Fix: Plugin documentation link.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0.1</h4>\n<p>Released Apr 22 &#8211; 2015</p>\n<ul>\n<li>New: Support to WordPress 4.2.</li>\n<li>Update: Plugin Core.</li>\n<li>Fix: Form for variation product.</li>\n<li>Fix: Send mail for variation product.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0.0</h4>\n<p>Released Mar 31 &#8211; 2015</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Initial release</li>\n</ul>\n";s:3:"faq";s:287:"\n<h4>Installation Instructions</h4>\n<p>\n<ol>\n<li>Unzip the downloaded zip file.</li>\n<li>Upload the plugin folder into the <code>wp-content/plugins/</code> directory of your WordPress site.</li>\n<li>Activate <code>YITH WooCommerce Waiting List</code> from Plugins page.</li>\n</ol>\n</p>\n\n";s:11:"screenshots";s:823:"<ol><li><a href="https://ps.w.org/yith-woocommerce-waiting-list/assets/screenshot-1.jpg?rev=1625824"><img src="https://ps.w.org/yith-woocommerce-waiting-list/assets/screenshot-1.jpg?rev=1625824" alt="The plugin admin page."></a><p>The plugin admin page.</p></li><li><a href="https://ps.w.org/yith-woocommerce-waiting-list/assets/screenshot-2.jpg?rev=1625824"><img src="https://ps.w.org/yith-woocommerce-waiting-list/assets/screenshot-2.jpg?rev=1625824" alt="Plugin frontend for logged in user"></a><p>Plugin frontend for logged in user</p></li><li><a href="https://ps.w.org/yith-woocommerce-waiting-list/assets/screenshot-3.jpg?rev=1625824"><img src="https://ps.w.org/yith-woocommerce-waiting-list/assets/screenshot-3.jpg?rev=1625824" alt="Plugin frontend for guest user"></a><p>Plugin frontend for guest user</p></li></ol>";}s:17:"short_description";s:112:"This plugin enables registered users to request an email notification when an out-of-stock product comes&hellip;";s:13:"download_link";s:78:"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/yith-woocommerce-waiting-list.1.2.0.zip";s:11:"screenshots";a:3:{i:1;a:2:{s:3:"src";s:82:"https://ps.w.org/yith-woocommerce-waiting-list/assets/screenshot-1.jpg?rev=1625824";s:7:"caption";s:22:"The plugin admin page.";}i:2;a:2:{s:3:"src";s:82:"https://ps.w.org/yith-woocommerce-waiting-list/assets/screenshot-2.jpg?rev=1625824";s:7:"caption";s:34:"Plugin frontend for logged in user";}i:3;a:2:{s:3:"src";s:82:"https://ps.w.org/yith-woocommerce-waiting-list/assets/screenshot-3.jpg?rev=1625824";s:7:"caption";s:30:"Plugin frontend for gu