ITH WooCommerce Product Add-Ons";s:4:"slug";s:32:"yith-woocommerce-product-add-ons";s:15:"premium_constat";s:17:"YITH_WAPO_PREMIUM";s:4:"file";s:8:"init.php";s:7:"wp_info";a:26:{s:4:"name";s:32:"YITH WooCommerce Product Add-Ons";s:4:"slug";s:32:"yith-woocommerce-product-add-ons";s:7:"version";s:5:"1.1.1";s:6:"author";s:43:"<a href="http://yithemes.com/">YITHEMES</a>";s:14:"author_profile";s:39:"https://profiles.wordpress.org/yithemes";s:8:"requires";s:3:"4.4";s:6:"tested";s:5:"4.9.4";s:12:"requires_php";b:0;s:6:"rating";d:64;s:7:"ratings";a:5:{i:5;i:4;i:4;i:0;i:3;i:2;i:2;i:0;i:1;i:3;}s:11:"num_ratings";i:9;s:15:"support_threads";i:18;s:24:"support_threads_resolved";i:2;s:15:"active_installs";i:4000;s:10:"downloaded";i:32802;s:12:"last_updated";s:21:"2017-12-12 9:11am GMT";s:5:"added";s:10:"2016-05-20";s:8:"homepage";s:0:"";s:8:"sections";a:5:{s:11:"description";s:2507:"<p>With YITH WooCommerce Product Add-ons you&#8217;ll be able to increase your customers&#8217; propensity to spend more and you&#8217;ll be able to cut off time dedicated to managing additional options for each product separately. How? Let&#8217;s imagine you have a jewellery store and one of your customers is going to purchase a ring: if variations can let them decide whether they prefer it in gold, silver or copper, how can you let them have a brief sentence carved on it and associate an extra cost to this in product page? YITH Product Add-ons allows you either to add a text field where your users can enter their sentence or select the one you have already configured for them through checkboxes or radio buttons in product page. And you&#8217;ll forget about long and messy email correspondences where the risk to mix up orders from different customers is just around the corner.</p>\n<p><strong>Features:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Create groups of options And choose to use them for all products of the shop, only for specific categories or limited on a single product</li>\n<li>Choose from different options Checkbox and Radio button</li>\n<li>Set dependency between the options To show a dropdown option only to users who selected the one that depends on it</li>\n<li>Increase the cost of product by assigning a fixed price to any of the options selected by user</li>\n<li>Specify single options By setting label and description</li>\n<li>Show a tooltip for the product add-ons</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Suggestions</h3>\n<p>If you have any suggestions about how to improve YITH WooCommerce Product Add-Ons, you can <a href="mailto:&#112;&#108;&#x75;&#x67;&#x69;&#x6e;&#x73;&#064;&#121;&#105;&#116;&#104;&#x65;&#x6d;&#x65;&#x73;&#x2e;&#099;&#111;&#109;" title="Your Inspiration\nThemes">write us</a><br />\nso we can bundle them into the next plugin release.</p>\n<h3>Translators</h3>\n<p>If you can&#8217;t find this plugin in your language and want to translate it, use the dedicated tool at [Translating WordPress] (https://translate<br />\n.wordpress.org/locale/it/default/wp-plugins/yith-pre-order-for-woocommerce &#8220;Translating WordPress&#8221;).<br />\nOr, if you have created your own language pack, or have an update for an existing one, you can send it as an email attachment from our [Contacts page] (http://yithemes.com/contact/ &#8220;Your Inspiration Themes&#8221;) and we will bundle into YITH WooCommerce Product Add-Ons.</p>\n<h4>Available Languages</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>English</li>\n<li>Italian</li>\n</ul>\n";s:12:"installation";s:645:"<p>Important: First of all, you have to download and activate WooCommerce plugin, which is mandatory for YITH WooCommerce Product Add-Ons to be working.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Unzip the downloaded zip file.</li>\n<li>Upload the plugin folder into the <code>wp-content/plugins/</code> directory of your WordPress site.</li>\n<li>Activate <code>YITH WooCommerce Product Add-Ons</code> from Plugins page.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>Configuration</h4>\n<p>YITH WooCommerce Product Add-Ons will add a new tab called &#8220;Products Add-Ons&#8221; in &#8220;YIT Plugins&#8221; menu item. There, you will find all Yithemes plugins with quick access to plugin setting page.</p>\n";s:3:"faq";s:1358:"\n<h4>Installation Instructions</h4>\n<p>\n<p>Important: First of all, you have to download and activate WooCommerce plugin, which is mandatory for YITH WooCommerce Product Add-Ons to be working.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Unzip the downloaded zip file.</li>\n<li>Upload the plugin folder into the <code>wp-content/plugins/</code> directory of your WordPress site.</li>\n<li>Activate <code>YITH WooCommerce Product Add-Ons</code> from Plugins page.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>Configuration</h4>\n<p>YITH WooCommerce Product Add-Ons will add a new tab called &#8220;Products Add-Ons&#8221; in &#8220;YIT Plugins&#8221; menu item. There, you will find all Yithemes plugins with quick access to plugin setting page.</p>\n</p>\n<h4>Can I add options groups on variable products?</h4>\n<p>\n<p>Yes, the plugin allows to do it. Options can be configured globally on product, but not on single variation.</p>\n</p>\n<h4>Can I disable global options on single product?</h4>\n<p>\n<p>Yes, you can do it, but not singularly. From the product editing page, you can disable the use of &#8220;all&#8221; global options groups.</p>\n</p>\n<h4>I would like to show an option only when a specific combination of options chosen from users occurs. How can I do it?</h4>\n<p>\n<p>You must enable the dependency on the option you are interested in by inserting the name of options you want your users to select.</p>\n</p>\n\n";s:9:"changelog";s:1192:"<h4>1.1.1 &#8211; Dec 06, 2017</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>New: WordPress 4.9 support</li>\n<li>New: WoooCommerce 3.2 support</li>\n<li>Dev: Added trigger &#8216;yith_wapo_product_price_updated&#8217; to frontend js handling</li>\n<li>Fix: Select2 and SelectWoo error</li>\n<li>Fix: Minor bugs</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.1.0 &#8211; Nov 10, 2017</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>New: WordPress 4.7 support</li>\n<li>New: WooCommerce 3.2.x support</li>\n<li>New: WooCommerce 3.1.x support</li>\n<li>Update: Plugin framework</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0.6 &#8211; Apr 06, 2017</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Update: Plugin framework</li>\n<li>Fix: Failed opening &#8216;yit-woocommerce-compatibility.php&#8217; error</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0.5 &#8211; Apr 04, 2017</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>New: WooCommerce 3.0 support</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0.4</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>New: WordPress 4.7 support</li>\n<li>Fix: clicking label radio and checkbox buttons doesn&#8217; t selected</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0.3</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fix: checkbox issue with &#8220;the edge/internet explorer&#8221;</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0.2</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fix: Conflict with &#8220;Advanced Recent Posts&#8221; plugin</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0.1</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fix: Notice when WooCommerce is not activated</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0.0</h4>\n<p>Initial Release</p>\n";s:11:"screenshots";s:943:"<ol><li><a href="https://ps.w.org/yith-woocommerce-product-add-ons/assets/screenshot-1.png?rev=1629221"><img src="https://ps.w.org/yith-woocommerce-product-add-ons/assets/screenshot-1.png?rev=1629221" alt="Setting Options"></a><p>Setting Options</p></li><li><a href="https://ps.w.org/yith-woocommerce-product-add-ons/assets/screenshot-2.png?rev=1629221"><img src="https://ps.w.org/yith-woocommerce-product-add-ons/assets/screenshot-2.png?rev=1629221" alt="YITH WooCommerce Product Add-Ons in &quot;Add-Ons&quot; edit page"></a><p>YITH WooCommerce Product Add-Ons in "Add-Ons" edit page</p></li><li><a href="https://ps.w.org/yith-woocommerce-product-add-ons/assets/screenshot-3.png?rev=1629221"><img src="https://ps.w.org/yith-woocommerce-product-add-ons/assets/screenshot-3.png?rev=1629221" alt="YITH WooCommerce Product Add-Ons in &quot;Single Prodcut&quot; page"></a><p>YITH WooCommerce Product Add-Ons in "Single Prodcut" page</p></li></ol>";}s:17:"short_description";s:99:"Increase average order value by letting your customers purchase additional options on your products";s:13:"download_link";s:81:"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/yith-woocommerce-product-add-ons.1.1.1.zip";s:11:"screenshots";a:3:{i: